                            <comment id="13205108" author="tlipcon" created="Fri, 10 Feb 2012 00:40:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Over in Accumulo land they have a neat framework called &quot;FATE&quot; (FAult Tolerant Execution or something?) Basically, they put up a znode in ZK for any master-coordinated action, and it acts as an &quot;intent log&quot; of the idempotent steps. If there&apos;s a failover, the new master will finish off any already-running FATE transaction.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13205120" author="liyin" created="Fri, 10 Feb 2012 00:46:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Cool! Sounds like what I try to do here. I will take a look over Accumulo.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13223349" author="stack" created="Tue, 6 Mar 2012 15:55:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolving as duplicate.  Liyin, you did it first so I should be resolving &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5494&quot; title=&quot;Introduce a zk hosted table-wide read/write lock so only one table operation at a time&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-5494&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-5494&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; as a duplicate of this but &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5494&quot; title=&quot;Introduce a zk hosted table-wide read/write lock so only one table operation at a time&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-5494&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-5494&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has a little bit more going on.  Hope you don&apos;t mind.   Are you working on this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13267667" author="liyin" created="Thu, 3 May 2012 18:30:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure. I am glad that Alex is working this jira right now and I will help on the code-review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
